A logistical pulsar search pipeline using Scott Ransom's PRESTO.

A brief listing of contents:
----------------------------
PALFA.zaplist           - A list of frequencies to zap from the power spectrum 
                            (in PRESTO-readable format)

PALFA2_presto_search.py - Search script for PALFA2.0 (MockSpec) data.

PALFA_presto_search.py  - Search script for PALFA (WAPP) data.

README                  - This read-me file

config.py               - Survey-specific configurations and preferences

job.py                  - Definition of PulsarSearchJob, JobLog and LogEntry objects

psrfits.py              - Definition of SpecInfo object for collecting useful 
                            information from PSR FITS files.

search.py               - Logistical search script that calls one of the 
                            *_presto_search.py scripts.

background.py           - Background script for running pulsar search jobs.


Dependencies:
-------------
PRESTO, a suite of pulsar search programs by Scott Ransom.
    - Available on GitHub: http://github.com/scottransom/presto
    - Python scripts and wrappers must be set up. (See PRESTO's documentation.)

pySLALIB, python wrappers for SLALIB created by Scott Ransom.
    - Available at: http://www.cv.nrao.edu/~sransom/

pbs_python, python wrappers for PBS created by sara.nl
    - Available at: http://subtrac.sara.nl/oss/pbs_python/wiki/TorqueInstallation


About:
